    "By reflecting on the case of Hong Kong, practical recommendations are given in this study.",
    "As the new academic year is going to begin soon, the authors hope that universities can be better prepared to make the transition of the new technologies easier for both teachers and students.",
    "Additionally, some countries banned the use of ChatGPT, but it can be foreseen that similar software will soon appear in those areas, and it is a matter of time for those universities to face similar struggles.",
    "It is believed that this study would bring both research and practical insights to the field.3 [ 28] ( 3)•3283 Mar 2023 HKUST • The use of ChatGPT is determined by the faculty and staff themselves Yiu [58] (1) 3 Mar 2023 CUHK • The use of AI tools such as ChatGPT to complete assignments is prohibited unless students have obtained explicit permission from their teachers Yiu [58] (1) 11 Mar 2023 CUHK • A student was caught using ChatGPT to do the assignment [25] (1) 13 Mar 2023 CUHK • Published a guide for students \"Use of Artificial Intelligence Tools in Teaching, Learning and Assessments: A Guide for Students\" Yiu [59](1) • Enhance the VeriGuide system, and plagiarism detection software, and develop other appropriate measures to analyze students' work 14 Mar 2023 HKUST • Some courses are encouraging students to use ChatGPT for their mid-term reports, with the incentive of receiving extra credit Fung [17] (1) • The HKUST management team want their student to learn how to use ChatGPT as soon as possible 23 Mar 2023 EdUHK • Allow students to use ChatGPT in all classes as long as they state the source in their work Hu [23] (9) • Planning to integrate AI elements into its general education curriculum • Releasing a set of 6-P pedagogical approaches on the use of generative AI for faculty staff 29 Mar 2023 HK Legislative Council • Confirmed only 5 out of 8 public universities in Hong Kong explicitly explained their position and regulations on ChatGPT to teaching staff and students (CUHK, LU, EdUHK, HKU, HKUST) [21] (2) 15 April 2023 HKU • Allowing staff to use ChatGPT for free for trial from April 17 to June 30 Students may be able to use ChatGPT after establishing policy and guidelines from the institution, temporary ban has not been lifted 2 May 2023 PolyU • Published Guidelines for Students on the Use of Generative Artificial Intelligence Table 11Summarized timeline according to the selected newspaper articles (n = 31) DateHighlights of the News articleInstitutio